        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 12:16AM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 1215 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles northeast of Olive Hill to near Canaan.
Movement was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Riverton, Wright, Threet, Waterloo, and Zip City.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 500 AM CDT for northwestern
Alabama.</instruction>
